"title": "5573: table",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5573",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>An item of furniture used principally for putting food on. Sharing at the same table was a mark of fellowship and to eat at the table of rulers was deemed a great privilege. In the tabernacle and temple a special table held the bread of the Presence. Tables were also used for business transactions.</p>\n<h2>Tables used for eating</h2>\n<h3>A table as household furniture</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:10\">2KI 4:10</a></p>\n<h3>Reclining at table</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:36\">LUK 7:36</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:7\">MAT 26:7</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:3\">MRK 14:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:37\">LUK 11:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:2\">JHN 12:2</a></p>\n<h3>Tables set for meals</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps23:5\">PSA 23:5</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa21:5\">ISA 21:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job36:16\">JOB 36:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:22\">PSA 69:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:19\">PSA 78:19</a> <em>The people of Israel doubted God's ability to provide</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov9:2\">PRO 9:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek23:41\">EZK 23:41</a></p>\n<h3>Giving thanks for food at the table</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:30\">LUK 24:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:26-Matt26:27\">MAT 26:26–26:27</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:22-Mark14:23\">MRK 14:22–14:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:17-Luke22:19\">LUK 22:17–22:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:23-1Cor11:24\">1CO 11:23–11:24</a></p>\n<h3>Dogs eat scraps from the table</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:27\">MAT 15:27</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:28\">MRK 7:28</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg1:7\">JDG 1:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:21\">LUK 16:21</a></p>\n<h2>Eating at the table of rulers</h2>\n<h3>Rulers were required to entertain</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh5:17-Neh5:18\">NEH 5:17–5:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs4:27\">1KI 4:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs10:4-1Kgs10:5\">1KI 10:4–10:5</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr9:3-2Chr9:4\">2CH 9:3–9:4</a></p>\n<h3>A bestowal of authority</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:29-Luke22:30\">LUK 22:29–22:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:2-Matt22:3\">MAT 22:2–22:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:15\">LUK 14:15</a></p>\n<h3>A mark of honour and favour</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen43:34\">GEN 43:34</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam9:11\">2SA 9:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs2:7\">1KI 2:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:19\">1KI 18:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs25:28-2Kgs25:29\">2KI 25:28–25:29</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer52:32-Jer52:33\">JER 52:32–52:33</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:7\">LUK 14:7</a> <em>Jesus Christ criticises those who seek the most prestigious places at the table.</em></p>\n<h2>Sharing at the same table was a mark of fellowship</h2>\n<h3>A sign of participation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:16-1Cor10:20\">1CO 10:16–10:20</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Unacceptable table fellowship</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan1:5-Dan1:8\">DAN 1:5–1:8</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:21\">1CO 10:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam20:34\">1SA 20:34</a> <em>Jonathan refuses to eat with Saul</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:19\">1KI 18:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:11\">ISA 65:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer7:18\">JER 7:18</a></p>\n<h3>Betrayal of table fellowship</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps41:9\">PSA 41:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam20:29-1Sam20:31\">1SA 20:29–20:31</a> <em>Saul wishes to kill David while inviting him to share his table</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan11:27\">DAN 11:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:20-Matt26:21\">MAT 26:20–26:21</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:18\">MRK 14:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:21\">LUK 22:21</a></p>\n<h2>Serving at table</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:27\">LUK 22:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:37\">LUK 12:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:2\">ACT 6:2</a> <em>The first Christians recognised the importance of practical service by appointing deacons to “wait on tables”.</em></p>\n<h2>Tables used in business</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:14-John2:15\">JHN 2:14–2:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:12\">MAT 21:12</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:15\">MRK 11:15</a></p>\n<h2>Tables used in worship</h2>\n<h3>The table in the tabernacle</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:23-Exod25:30\">EXO 25:23–25:30</a></strong> <em>The table was for the bread of the Presence: an offering of twelve loaves, one from each of the twelve tribes.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod37:10-Exod37:16\">EXO 37:10–37:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod26:35\">EXO 26:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:27\">EXO 30:27</a> <em>The table was anointed for use</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:13\">EXO 35:13</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:36\">EXO 39:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:4\">EXO 40:4</a>NUM <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:31\">3:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:7\">NUM 4:7</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:2\">HEB 9:2</a></p>\n<h3>The tables in Solomon's temple</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr4:8\">2CH 4:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs7:48\">1KI 7:48</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr4:19\">2CH 4:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr28:16\">1CH 28:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr13:11\">2CH 13:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr29:18\">2CH 29:18</a></p>\n<h3>The tables in Ezekiel's temple</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:39-Ezek40:43\">EZK 40:39–40:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek41:22\">EZK 41:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek44:16\">EZK 44:16</a></p>\n<h3>Tables in worship after the exile</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr9:31-1Chr9:32\">1CH 9:31–9:32</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:33\">NEH 10:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal1:7\">MAL 1:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal1:12\">MAL 1:12</a></p>",
